WHEREAS, the university continues to be guided by its well-known motto, "Where
Everybody is Somebody", which is a guiding principle that reflects its longstanding
commitment to human dignity, educational opportunity, and the development of every
student; and
WHEREAS, the celebration of Grambling State University's one hundred
twenty-fifth anniversary is an appropriate opportunity to recognize the school's historic
legacy and continuing importance to the people of Louisiana.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
commend Grambling State University upon the celebration of the one hundred twenty-fifth
anniversary of its founding and does hereby recognize the university for its extraordinary
and lasting contributions to higher education, leadership, and public service.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby extend
its sincere best wishes to the students, faculty, staff, alumni, administration, and supporters
of Grambling State University as they commemorate this historic milestone and continue the
institution's proud legacy of excellence.
